    • Constructor Detail

      • CustomHead

        public CustomHead(UUID uuid,
                  String spawnName,
                  String displayName,
                  String textureUrlB64,
                  List<String> lore)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a custom head type with information required to create, display, spawn, and detect the head. This class does not invoke any Bukkit methods and only stores information, but it does require the API to be available.
        Parameters:
        uuid - the internal ID used in the custom head's owner field, for detection. This value should be unique to your head (randomly created), but never change. It must not match other head UUIDs.
        spawnName - the string players can use to spawn your head with the command /ph spawn #spawnnamehere
        displayName - the custom display-name (title) of the head displayed as the item name and when clicking heads for information.
        textureUrlB64 - the base64-encoded texture json + URL
        lore - the loretext to display, or null for the default PlayerHeads loretext.

      • CustomHead

        @Deprecated
public CustomHead(UUID uuid,
                               String ownerName,
                               String spawnName,
                               String displayName,
                               String textureUrlB64,
                               List<String> lore)
        Deprecated. custom heads should avoid using owner usernames whenever possible.
        Constructs a custom head type with information required to create, display, spawn, and detect the head. This class does not invoke any Bukkit methods and only stores information, but it does require the API to be available.
        Parameters:
        uuid - the internal ID used in the custom head's owner field, for detection. This value should be unique to your head (randomly created), but never change. It must not match other head UUIDs.
        ownerName - the owner name to set (optionally) for the head.
        spawnName - the string players can use to spawn your head with the command /ph spawn #spawnnamehere
        displayName - the custom display-name (title) of the head displayed as the item name and when clicking heads for information.
        textureUrlB64 - the base64-encoded texture json + URL
        lore - the loretext to display, or null for the default PlayerHeads loretext.
